28  \details
29 
30  This [omdl] formatted data table has been assembled using a script
31  that converts the polyhedra data obtained from [Anthony Thyssen]'s
32  [Studies into Polyhedra]. The vertices are tabulated in both their
33  original Cartesian as well as their converted spherical coordinate
34  form, which is convenient when scaling. The data originates from
35  one of three sources:
36 
37  \li [Exact Mathematics] as presented by [Anthony Thyssen],
38  \li the [Polyhedron Database] maintained by [Netlib], and
39  \li an [Encyclopedia of Polyhedra] by [George W. Hart].
40 
41  \note Include this library file using the \b include statement.
42 
43  [omdl]: https://github.com/royasutton/omdl
44 
45  [Anthony Thyssen]: http://www.ict.griffith.edu.au/anthony/anthony.html
46  [Studies into Polyhedra]: http://www.ict.griffith.edu.au/anthony/graphics/polyhedra
47  [Exact Mathematics]: http://www.ict.griffith.edu.au/anthony/graphics/polyhedra/maths.shtml
48 
49  [George W. Hart]: http://www.georgehart.com
50  [Encyclopedia of Polyhedra]: http://www.georgehart.com/virtual-polyhedra/vp.html
51 
52  [Netlib]: http://www.netlib.org
53  [Polyhedron Database]: http://www.netlib.org/polyhedra
54 
55  \ingroup database_polyhedra
56 *******************************************************************************/
57 
58 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------//
59 /***************************************************************************//**
60  \addtogroup database_geometry
61  @{
62 
63  \defgroup database_polyhedra Polyhedra
64  \brief Tables of polyhedra vertices, faces, and edges.
65 
66  \details
67 
68  Database of polyhedra vertices, faces, and edges. Classes of
69  polyhedra are grouped into separate files. The file
70  polyhedra_all.scad contains all polyhedra from all files. Each
71  table uses the following column data structure.
72 
73  | feild | description |
74  |:-----:|:--------------------|
75  | id | identifier |
76  | n | name |
77  | o | other name |
78  | g | group |
79  | d | data source |
80  | c | cartesian vertices |
81  | s | spherical vertices |
82  | f | faces |
83  | e | edges |
84 
85  Use the functions get_table_v() to retrieve feild data as show in
86  the following example. To see a list of table identifiers consider
87  the function get_table_ridl(), get_table_cidl(), or module
88  table_dump(). See datatypes_table.scad for other available table
89  functions.
90 
91  \b Example
92  \code{.C}
93  include <units/units_coordinate.scad>;
94  include <tools/tools_polytope.scad>;
95  include <datatypes/datatypes_table.scad>;
96  include <database/geometry/polyhedra/platonic.scad>;
97 
98  tc = dtc_polyhedra_platonic;
99  tr = dtr_polyhedra_platonic;
100 
101  id = "dodecahedron";
102 
103  pv = get_table_v(tr, tc, id, "c");
104  pf = get_table_v(tr, tc, id, "f");
105 
106  sv = coordinates_csc(pv, 100);
107 
108  polytope_number(sv, pf, to=[0,0,5]);
109  polytope_frame(sv, pf) {circle(r=2); color("grey") sphere(r=4);}
110  polyhedron(sv, pf);
111  \endcode
112 
113  \b Autotests \include polyhedra_all_db_autotest.log
114 
115  For more information see Wikipedia on [Polyhedron].
116 
117  [Polyhedron]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polyhedron
118 
119  @{
120 *******************************************************************************/
121 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------//

21499 BEGIN_SCOPE db;
21500 BEGIN_SCOPE autotest;
21501  BEGIN_OPENSCAD;
21502  include <math/math_polytope.scad>;
21503  include <units/units_coordinate.scad>;
21504  include <datatypes/datatypes_table.scad>;
21505  include <database/geometry/polyhedra/polyhedra_all.scad>;
21506 
21507  coordinates_positive_angles = false;
21508 
21509  tc = dtc_polyhedra_polyhedra_all;
21510  tr = dtr_polyhedra_polyhedra_all;
21511 
21512  log_echo("checking table: ");
21513  log_echo("colums = dtc_polyhedra_polyhedra_all");
21514  log_echo(" rows = dtr_polyhedra_polyhedra_all");
21515  table_check (tr, tc, verbose=true);
21516 
21517  echo();
21518  log_echo("confirming calculations stored in table:");
21519  log_echo(" (1) spherical with converted cartesian coordinates:");
21520  log_echo(" (2) edge list from faces definition:");
21521 
21522  for ( id = get_table_ridl( tr ) )
21523  {
21524  c = get_table_v(tr, tc, id, "c");
21525  s = get_table_v(tr, tc, id, "s");
21526  f = get_table_v(tr, tc, id, "f");
21527  e = get_table_v(tr, tc, id, "e");
21528 
21529  // convert stored spherical and compare with cartesian coordinates.
21530  for( i = [0 : len(c)-1] )
21531  {
21532  cc = convert_coordinate(s[i], from="s");
21533 
21534  if ( !n_almost_equal(c[i], cc) )
21535  {
21536  cs = convert_coordinate(c[i], to="s");
21537 
21538  n = get_table_v(tr, tc, id, "n");
21539  o = get_table_v(tr, tc, id, "o");
21540  g = get_table_v(tr, tc, id, "g");
21541  d = get_table_v(tr, tc, id, "d");
21542 
21543  log_warn("coordinate mismatch");
21544  log_info(str("id=", id,", n=", n, ", o=", o, ", g=", g, ", d=", d));
21545  echo(i=i, dt_c=c[i], c_c=cc, dt_s=s[i], c_s=cs);
21546  }
21547  }
21548 
21549  // re-create sorted edge list and compare with stored.
21550  ce = qsort2(polytope_faces2edges(f, d=1), d=1);
21551 
21552  if ( e != ce )
21553  {
21554  se = qsort2(e, d=1);
21555  if ( se == ce )
21556  {
21557  log_info(str("edge-list not sorted: id=", id));
21558  }
21559  else
21560  {
21561  n = get_table_v(tr, tc, id, "n");
21562  o = get_table_v(tr, tc, id, "o");
21563  g = get_table_v(tr, tc, id, "g");
21564  d = get_table_v(tr, tc, id, "d");
21565 
21566  log_warn("edge-list mismatch");
21567  log_info(str("id=", id,", n=", n, ", o=", o, ", g=", g, ", d=", d));
21568  echo(l=len(e), dt_e=e);
21569  echo(l=len(se), st_e=se);
21570  echo(l=len(ce), cl_e=ce);
21571  }
21572  }
21573  }
21574 
21575  echo();
21576  log_echo(str(get_table_size(tr)," polyhedra checked."));
